description:
&lt;p&gt;If you are looking for a career in Cardiothoracic nursing, this is your chance to join a friendly supportive team at Harefield hospital. Situated 20 miles to the west of London.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The HDU is a 10 bedded level 2 area. We are part of critical care which consists of 24 Level 3 beds and 5 Level 3 beds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our HDU cares for patients following a variety of complex cardiothoracic procedures. Successful applicants will be fully supported whilst gaining experience in the care of critically ill patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our education programmes, supported by our practice education team, aim to provide staff of all grades with the essential knowledge and skills required in our busy, friendly department. Following orientation and completion of step one Clinical competencies, staff will have the opportunity to access university-based post-graduate courses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for highly motivated individuals who have excellent care values, a strong sense of team spirit and are keen to develop their skills, delivering high quality care in this exciting area. Previous experience within critical care is desirable (pre-registration placements included).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For informal enquires/information, please contact Claire Fountain/Lynne Soames, Senior Sisters HDU at Harefield on 0330 128 88572.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
